==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aroint
<hw>A*roint"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*roint")</pr>, <pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
Prov. E. <ets>rynt</ets>, <ets>rynt</ets> thee, <ets>roynt</ets>, or
<ets>runt</ets>, terms used by milkmaids to a cow that has been milked,
in order to drive her away, to make room for others; AS.
<ets>r⟦ymac⟧man</ets> to make room or way, fr. <ets>r⟦umac⟧m</ets> room.
The final <it>t</it> is perh. for <ets>ta</ets>, for <ets>thou</ets>.
Cf. <er>Room</er> space.]</ety> <def>Stand off, or begone.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Aroint</qex> thee, witch, the rump-fed ronyon cries.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

